S:
  1:Bootstrap a bundle — `mkdir my-knowledge-bundle && mkdir -p tables metrics runbooks concepts api`
  2:Author an atom — add YAML frontmatter (type/title/description + optional resource/tags/timestamp) + Markdown body (Overview, Schema, Examples, Joins, Citations)
  3:Cross-link atoms — use absolute bundle-root links `/tables/customers.md` (recommended) or relative `./other.md`
  4:Validate — run the bundled Python linter; checks type/title/description presence in all OKF .md files
  5:Distribute — tarball, git repo (recommended for freshness via timestamp), or filesystem mount
  6:Consume — walk bundle with pyyaml, filter by frontmatter.type, inject relevant atoms into agent context
  7:Integrate with llm-wiki — promote raw wiki captures to OKF format (add required frontmatter + organize into typed subdirectories)
  8:Plugin install — `npx skills add https://github.com/akillness/jeo-skills --skill okf`
